properties.text: Heaven's Point never hid their disgust of the inhabitants of Castle Moss, and their barbaric ways.
Castle Moss was once a sanctuary, where the Moss-Knights venerated only nature.
Until recently, Castle Baron was known as Castle Thornburg, after the former ruler of the castle.
Thaea, the goddess of fertility and harvests, was the mother of all the woodland creatures, and the mother of the other gods worshipped by the Druids of Castle Moss.
Wielding the power of elemental magic, the Druids of Castle Moss lived in harmony with nature, worshiping multiple deities.
Castle Moss outnumbered Heaven's Point two to one, but it did not matter, for Castle Moss didn't have the angelic power behind them.

A moot was called, and representatives from Castle Moss, Heaven's Point, and Castle Thornburg were to attend at the summit of the Penitent Tower. It was here that the Angels ordered the Moss-Knights to give up their druidic ways, or perish. This was called the Dissodian Summit.
